Background

		Mr. H. Sanford Riley, also known as Sandy, CM, OM, LLD, J.D., has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Richardson Financial Group Limited since 2003. Mr. Riley serves as the Managing Director of Richardson Capital Limited. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Investors Group, Inc. from 1992 to 2001. He serves as the Chairman of Richardson Partners Financial Holdings Limited and Manitoba Hydro-Electric Board. He served as the Chairman ... of The North West Company, Inc. since June 2008 and served as its Independent Director since 2003. He served as the Chairman of Richardson Partners Financial Limited. He served as the Chairman of Investors Group Inc. from 2001 to 2003. He has been a Director of London Insurance Group Inc. and Molson Coors Brewing Company since February 2005. He has been an Independent Director of Manitoba Telecom Services, Inc. since May 4, 2011 and Canadian Western Bank since March 3, 2011. He has been Corporate Director of Molson Inc. since June 29, 1999. He serves as a Director of Fraser Institute and Allstream Inc. He serves as a Director of CentreVenture Development Corp. and James Richardson & Sons affiliated companies. He served as an Independent Director at GMP Capital Inc. from November 2009 to April 28, 2017. He serves as the Chancellor of the University of Winnipeg. He served as a Director of IGM Financial Inc., The Great-West Life Assurance Company since November 26, 1997 and Great-West Lifeco Inc. since November 1997. He served as a Director of Winnipeg Airports Authority Inc. since February 2011. He serves as a Member of Investment Committee at Capital for Aboriginal Prosperity and Entrepreneurship and serves as a Director of the Canada West Foundation, the Manitoba Business Council and Canada's National History Society. He was appointed as a Member of the Order of Canada in 2002. He served as Chairman of the Manitoba Business Council. He served as the Chancellor of the University of Winnipeg and Chairman of University of Winnipeg Foundation. He obtained a B.A. from Queen's University and an LL.B Degree from Osgoode Hall Law School.Read Full Background




